{{c|vdev}} is another [[device file]] manager. According to its author, it is intended to strike a balance between the approaches of {{c|[[mdev]]}} and {{c|[[udev]]}} (or {{c|[[eudev]]}}) in terms of how much work the user is required to do.<ref>[https://forums.gentoo.org/viewtopic-t-1008306.html#7678892 Comment in Gentoo Forums: Discussing vdev from Devuan Project], by judecn, Wed Jan 07, 2015 4:00 am.</ref>

== Installation ==

An ebuild for {{c|sys-fs/vdev}} is available from [https://github.com/tokiclover/bar-overlay.git bar-overlay].

{{FileBox|filename=[[:/etc/portage/repos.conf]]/bar.conf|lang=bash|1=
location = /usr/local/overlay/bar
sync-type = git
sync-uri = git://github.com/tokiclover/bar-overlay.git
auto-sync = yes}}

{{RootCmd|emaint sync -r bar}}

